content.location:
It is the fifth set of anchors from the north on the Ripple Wall.  It is just left of a block at the base of the cliff (which is the start for

Baja Ha Ha

).

content.description:
A great, high angle, slab climb, it's all about the feet.  The route alternates between smearing, ripple holds, and horizontal breaks.  Limited handholds on the start.  After the start, follow the rock incursion up and to the left.  Then, follow a vertical crack to the anchors.  (if you keep following the incursion, you'll be on

Eddyline

).  2 cruxes: shortly after the start and right before the end.
